notes: This report provides the information requested in Term 5 which states : "Permittee/licensee shall measure and report the volume and time of releases and bypass from Dorris Â·Reservoir, the elevation of water levels, the volume of water held in Dorris Reservoir and evaporation from Dorris Reservoir. Using these measurements and any other measurements that may be necessary,  permittee/licensee shall calculate the volume of water stored in Dorris Reservoir, the volume of water directly diverted through Dorris Reservoir, and the contributions to storage and direct diversion from (1) Parker Creek, (2) Pine Creek and (3) Stockdill Slough."  Table 1 of this report provides monthly summaries of this information for the 1995 water year. Appendix A explains the notation and calculations used. Appendix B provides flood flow documentation.
